{"command": "write", "path": "/go-game/README.md", "content": "# Simple Go Game

A basic implementation of the ancient board game Go (also known as Weiqi or Baduk) in Python.

## Features

- 9x9 board size (simplified for beginners)
- Two-player turn-based gameplay
- Basic move validation
- Pass functionality
- Score counting at the end of the game

## How to Play

1. Clone this repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/test/go-game.git
   cd go-game
   ```

2. Run the game:
   ```bash
   python main.py
   ```

3. During gameplay:
   - Enter coordinates as "x y" (e.g., "3 4" to place a stone at row 3, column 4)
   - Type "pass" to skip your turn
   - The game ends when both players pass consecutively
   - Final scores are counted and the winner is announced

## Game Rules (Simplified)

- Black plays first
- Players take turns placing stones on empty intersections
- Once placed, stones cannot be moved
- The game ends when both players pass consecutively
- Score is counted by the number of stones on the board (simplified scoring)

## Requirements

- Python 3.x

## Note

This is a simplified version of Go that doesn't implement:
- Capturing stones
- Ko rule
- Territory scoring
- Handicap stones

It's designed as an educational introduction to the game mechanics."}
